reviews.review_text:
Wow. What a spacey, intense second set.  Playing gets way out there, as does Wharf Rat:  the first WR solo is beyond wild.  

This new seed is really nice, too.  Put on headphones and you are there!
oh,wow oh,wow,this here is most exellent,I just listened to the 2nd set and I have to say....well,what can I say?..the music play's the band....5 stars don't cover it
Garcia's voice Absolutely love jerry's paper thin, frail voice! sound quaility is  bit low
Levels need boosting This is a good quality aud.  Just wish the levels were a bit higher.  Forgettable first set but Terrapin-Playin, esp the later, are great.

Read more about this show There is a great blog post about this show posted here by an attendee:

http://lostlivedead.blogspot.com/2012/04/january-15-1978-selland-arena-fresno-ca.html

He discusses the Dead's odd departure from their regular touring schedule to play shows in January, something they hadn't done since 1970. In all, this tour was a bust. Jerry's voice was marred by laryngitis, and shows were filled with Bobby-only tunes. Things start sounding better towards the end of the month, but, in all, it was a pretty lackluster outing.
